      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:1:13",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) الصَّلَاةُ مِيزَانٌ مَنْ وَفَّى اسْتَوْفَى ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Abdullah Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from his father, from Abdullah Bin Al Mugheira, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span> is a scale, the one who balances (it), would be Balanced with (on the Day of Judgement)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "13. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from his father from ‘Abd Allah ibn al-Mughirah formal-Sakuniy who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘Salah (prayer) is a balance. Whoever maintains it balanced receives his part properly balanced.  "
        ]
      }
    }
